definition: dish (type of food)/vegetable/cuisine/CL:盤|盘[pan2],道[dao4]/(coll.) (one's) type/(of one's skills etc) weak/poor

sentences.english: The garden, a variety of vegetables mother, dark green piece.
sentences.chinese: 花園裏，母親種的各樣菜蔬，碧綠一片。

sentences.english: The salty variety is filled with minced meat, vegetables etc.
sentences.chinese: 鹹餡則可以由碎肉末，菜蔬等做成。

sentences.english: Just as I gave you the green plants, I now give you everything.
sentences.chinese: 這一切我都賜給你們，如同菜蔬一樣。

sentences.english: The second deficit in v. 5 was that there was no herb in the field.
sentences.chinese: 第五節中的第二個缺失是田間的菜蔬還沒有長起來。

sentences.english: And did eat up all the herbs in their land, and devoured the fruit of their ground.
sentences.chinese: 吃盡了他們地上各樣的菜蔬，和田地的出產。

sentences.english: It's good to eat more vegetables.
sentences.chinese: 喫更多的菜蔬是有益的。

sentences.english: Thorns also and thistles shall it bring forth to thee； and thou shalt eat the herb of the field；
sentences.chinese: 地必給你長出荊棘和蒺藜來，你也要喫田間的菜蔬。

sentences.english: Americans have very simple lunches which are partly made of raw vegetables.
sentences.chinese: 美國人的午餐十分簡單，生的菜蔬是其中的一個部分。

sentences.english: 35 they ate up every green thing in their land, ate up the produce of their soil.
sentences.chinese: 吃盡了他們地上各樣的菜蔬，和田地的出產。

sentences.english: We have steak, roast chellocken and vegetables today.
sentences.chinese: 咱們今日供應牛肉片，烤雞以及菜蔬。

sentences.english: What kind of vegetables would you like?
